# Technical Specification: Dashboard v2 Feature Flag Rollout & Rollback Protocol

## 1. Executive Summary
**Objective:** Mitigate critical usability regressions identified in the Dashboard v2 release (40% session drop, 15% 404 errors, undefined API responses) by implementing a controlled, gradual feature flag rollout.
**Trigger:** Immediate halt of full exposure; transition to a phased canary deployment.
**Target System:** Frontend Dashboard Module (`/api/dashboard/v2`).

## 2. Feature Flag Configuration
**Flag Name:** `feat_dashboard_v2_rollout`
**Default State:** `OFF` (Force fallback to Dashboard v1).
**Rollout Strategy:** Percentage-based Canary Deployment.

### Rollout Schedule
| Phase | Target Audience | Percentage | Duration | Success Criteria |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Phase 0** | Internal QA/Staging | 0% | Immediate | System stable in staging. |
| **Phase 1** | Internal Engineering | 1% | 24 Hours | Zero critical JS errors; Session duration > 90% of baseline. |
| **Phase 2** | Beta Users | 5% | 48 Hours | 404 error rate < 0.5%; API response time < 200ms. |
| **Phase 3** | General Users (Tier 1) | 25% | 72 Hours | No regression in core widget rendering. |
| **Phase 4** | General Users (Tier 2) | 100% | TBD | Full stabilization. |

### Implementation Logic
```javascript
// Pseudo-code for Flag Evaluation
const isV2Enabled = featureFlagService.isEnabled('feat_dashboard_v2_rollout', user.id);

if (isV2Enabled) {
    // Attempt to load v2 widgets
    try {
        const data = await fetch('/api/dashboard/v2');
        if (!data || data.status === 404) {
            throw new Error('API v2 Unavailable');
        }
        renderDashboardV2(data);
    } catch (error) {
        // Automatic client-side fallback to v1 if v2 fails
        console.warn('V2 API failure, falling back to v1');
        renderDashboardV1();
    }
} else {
    // Force v1
    renderDashboardV1();
}
```

## 3. Rollback Plan & Incident Response
**Trigger Conditions for Immediate Rollback:**
1.  **Error Rate:** 404 or 500 errors on `/api/dashboard/v2` exceed 2% of total requests.
2.  **Performance:** Average session duration drops below 60% of the pre-release baseline.
3.  **User Feedback:** >500 support tickets filed within 1 hour regarding "missing widgets" or "broken dashboard."

### Rollback Procedure
1.  **Immediate Action:** Set `feat_dashboard_v2_rollout` to `OFF` globally via the Feature Flag Management Console.
2.  **Propagation:** Ensure flag state propagates to all edge nodes within 30 seconds (TTL: 30s).
3.  **Verification:** Monitor error logs for 5 minutes to confirm 404 errors cease and v1 widgets load successfully.

### RTO/RPO Metrics
| Metric | Definition | Target Value |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **RTO (Recovery Time Objective)** | Time from detection of critical failure to full restoration of v1 functionality. | **< 5 Minutes** |
| **RPO (Recovery Point Objective)** | Maximum acceptable data loss (User session state). | **0 Minutes** (Stateless fallback ensures no data loss; user session persists). |

## 4. Monitoring & Alerting
**Dashboard Alerts (Configured in Datadog/New Relic):**
*   **Alert 1:** `Error Rate > 2%` on endpoint `/api/dashboard/v2` (Severity: Critical).
*   **Alert 2:** `Session Duration < 60%` of baseline (Severity: High).
*   **Alert 3:** `404 Count > 1000` in 5-minute window (Severity: Critical).

**Action:** Automated PagerDuty escalation to the On-Call DevOps Engineer upon alert trigger.

## 5. Approval & Sign-off
*   **Prepared By:** Web Administration Team
*   **Approved By:** [Dev Lead Name], [Product Owner Name]
*   **Effective Date:** Immediate
*   **Next Review:** 24 hours post-Phase 1 completion.

